// Session Registry
// Persists collab sessions to ~/.mermaid-collab/sessions.json and manages session directory scaffolding.

Sessions are stored at .collab/sessions/{name}/ (new) or .collab/{name}/ (legacy).
Stale sessions (directories that no longer exist) are automatically removed on list().
A singleton instance (sessionRegistry) is exported for convenience.

FUNCTION constructor(registryPath)
  Accept an optional registry path; defaults to ~/.mermaid-collab/sessions.json.

---

FUNCTION createFileIfNotExists(filePath, content) -> void
  Private. IF the file does not exist, create its parent directory and write the content.

---

FUNCTION load() -> SessionRegistryData
  IF file does not exist, return empty { sessions: [] }.
  Read and parse JSON. IF structure is invalid, warn and return empty.

---

FUNCTION save(registry) -> void
  Create the parent directory if needed. Write serialized registry JSON.

---

FUNCTION register(project, session, sessionType, useRenderUI, initialState) -> { created }
  Validate that project is an absolute path and session is alphanumeric with hyphens.
  Load registry. IF session already exists for the project, update lastAccess.
  ELSE add a new entry.
  Ensure all session subdirectories exist: diagrams/, documents/, designs/, spreadsheets/, snippets/.
  Create collab-state.json if it does not yet exist (with state, sessionType, lastActivity, useRenderUI).
  Return { created: true/false }.

---

FUNCTION list() -> Session[]
  Load registry. For each session, check whether its directory exists in the new location,
  the todos location, or the old legacy location.
  Auto-remove stale entries, log removed names, and save if any were stale.
  Return valid sessions sorted by lastAccess descending.

---

FUNCTION resolvePath(project, session, type) -> string
  Validate inputs. Check new location (.collab/sessions/{session}/{type}) first.
  Then check the todos location (.collab/todos/{session}/{type}).
  Then check the legacy location (.collab/{session}/{type}).
  Return the first path that exists, or default to the new location if none exist.

---

FUNCTION ensureSnippetsDir(project, session) -> void
  Validate inputs. Create the snippets directory at the new location if it does not exist.

---

FUNCTION getSnippetsPath(project, session) -> string
  CALLS: resolvePath (session-registry)
  Return the resolved path for the snippets folder.

---

FUNCTION registerSnippet(project, session, snippetId, metadata) -> { success, id }
  CALLS: ensureSnippetsDir (session-registry)
  Validate all inputs. Ensure the snippets directory exists.
  Return { success: true, id: snippetId }. Actual snippet metadata is managed by SnippetManager.

---

FUNCTION unregisterSnippet(project, session, snippetId) -> boolean
  Validate inputs. This is a no-op at the registry level (file management is in SnippetManager).
  Return true.

---

FUNCTION getDisplayName(session) -> string
  Return "projectName / sessionName" using the basename of the project path.

---

FUNCTION unregister(project, session) -> boolean
  Load registry, filter out the matching entry, save if changed.
  Return true if removed, false if not found.
